  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Sarah Hilditch emphasizes the wrongness of the Evangelical Alliance in respect to anti-slavery feeling. The enthusiasm with which George Thompson, William Lloyd Garrison, and Frederick Douglass were received has proved that &quot;the Evangelical Alliance is not the British Public.&quot; These three were entertained in Sarah Hilditch&apos;s little town; the meeting was &quot;the best ever held in our town.&quot; Frederick Douglass &quot;has been working wonders.&quot; Sarah Hilditch is enthusiastic about William Lloyd Garrison. She praises George Thompson, who &quot;has had to expose some who were his dearest friends.&quot; Sarah Hilditch hopes to meet H. C. Wright next week.</subfield>
